             depos'd, that they went to the prisoner's House to bail the Deceased; that the Deceased begg'd of them to get her out, for she was afraid she should be murdered; adding, that the Prisoner had thrown her down Stairs. But being cross examin'd. Rimington said, that the next Day he heard the Deceased and Mrs. Hart ask the prisoner's pardon for assaulting him. 
               <persName id="t17211206-9-person90">
                  Alice 
                  Harly 
               <interp inst="t17211206-9-person90" type="surname" value="Harly"></interp>
